These photographs by, P.L. Sperr,

Thanksgiving Ragamuffins, 1933, No. 61, on the roof of the small building in Central Park next to the Columbus Circle entrance. The woman on the bench is looking up at them with possibly a touch of apprehension. The scene is the same as that of No. 60. November 30, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

No. 62. The same, another view. November 30, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

No. 63. The same two girls, on 61st Street near Columbus Avenue. They're boys, of course. November 30, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.
